						<summary>

						<p>Karivaradarāja-perumāḷ temple, central shrine, north wall.</p>						

						<p>••• ••• ••• •••</p>						

						<p>In late characters.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records that Puṇṇiyavāṭṭiyār, the wife of Irājarājaṉ-Vāṇakōvaraiyaṉ and daughter of Kuḻūruḍaiyāṉ Iraṇaṉ Kōvalarāyaṉ, carried out repairs in the <hi rend="italic">śrī-Vimānam</hi> (central shrine) and temple of Irājarāja-viṇṇagar (i.e.,) temple of Śrī-Perumāḷ. </p>						

						</summary>
